    "summary": "I am an Assistant Professor of Operations Research (with tenure) at the University of Twente, teaching in the bachelor and master programs of Industrial Engineering & Management. In my research, I develop optimization models and algorithms for solving complex decision making problems arising in the transportation, logistics, and energy sectors (e.g., operations, planning, and investments), often in collaboration with the industry. My technical expertise includes math programming, network algorithms, combinatorial optimization, and decision making under uncertainty with focus on reinforcement learning/approximate dynamic programming.",
